# Validation checklist

**Canonical checklist:** [`docs/validation-checklist.md`](../docs/validation-checklist.md) — lifecycle gates 0–6 ↔ `gate_status`, merge-ready **MG-01**–**MG-05**, handoff **PROJ-HANDOFF-*** (orchestration appendix; do not conflate)

## When to use

- **Validator agent:** Audit every **applicable** section before issuing `validation-report.md`. Record results in **Checklist audit** (item ID, status ✅ / ⚠️ / ❌ / N/A, evidence).
- **Planner:** Pull relevant rows into `plan.md` → **Validation commands**; map to AC IDs.
- **Human PR review:** Use the same IDs when reviewing changes that touch boundaries covered by the checklist.

## Verdict interaction

- Any applicable **❌** on **MG-*** or on a row required by `plan.md` / an **Accepted** ADR → **FAIL** (blocks **PASS_WITH_NOTES**) when the project defines that policy.
- Mark sections **N/A** with a one-line reason when the change does not touch that domain.

